Roy Keane has been summonsed to court after he was accused of a road rage rant with a taxi driver at a set of traffic lights.

The former Manchester United star has been ordered to attend Trafford Magistrates Court later this month for a Section 4A Public Order offence.

Ex-Sunderland and Ipswich Town manager Keane, currently Republic of Ireland coach, was said to have launched into a foul-mouthed tirade and made obscene gestures after jumping out his Range Rover in Altrincham, Greater Manchester.

